cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper focuses on computer vision tasks using deep learning and explores the use of computational cameras to reduce power consumption. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the accuracy of the binary gradient cameras, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses applications such as surveillance, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
